Module FloWeekTracker
Package com.floweektracker.view

Class TaskEditingDialog

java.lang.Object
com.floweektracker.view.TaskEditingDialog
public class TaskEditingDialog extends Object
UI of the task editing dialog that allows the user to edit a task in the planner. It enables to edit task name, weekday, time, description, done status and priority. At the bottom of the dialog, there are two buttons, which are used to confirm editing or cancel it.

Fields: originalTask, view, dialog, tasksComboBox, weekdaysComboBox, timeSpinner, descriptionTextArea, prioritySpinner, statusComboBox, buttons, isDialogOpen

Visibility methods: makeDialogVisible(SingleTask), setValuesFromOriginalTask(SingleTask), makeDialogInvisible()

Getter methods: getTaskName(), getDescription(), getWeekday(), getTime(), getPriority(), getStatus(), getAllTaskNames()

  • Method Details

    • makeDialogVisible

      public boolean makeDialogVisible(SingleTask originalTask)
      Makes dialog visible. Before it sets visibility as true, it marks isDialogOpen as false. Then, it checks if the given task is null. If it is, it shows message to the user. Otherwise, it sets values from original task to the dialog's components, sets location of the dialog to the center of the screen and finally makes dialog visible.
      See Also:
      • DialogUtils.showMessageDialog(String, String)
